&lt;h3 id="whats-cross-country-skiing" class="relative group"&gt;What’s cross-country skiing? &lt;span class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100"&gt;&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700" style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#whats-cross-country-skiing" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cross-country skiing (XC) is part of Nordic skiing and is done on prepared tracks (“loipes”) or off-track in the backcountry. You move using a combination of leg push and pole push, with skis that allow you to go both uphill and downhill.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Sunrise ski touring</title><link>https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/sunrise-ski-touring/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">https://mountaindiaries.com/posts/sunrise-ski-touring/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;When: Jan 30 2026&lt;br&gt;
Where: &lt;em&gt;Hochfügen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woke up at 4am to ski towards sunrise. Wished there were a bit more snow, but ski-touring before breakfast and work.&lt;/p&gt;
